node.title: Aleksandr Selevko of Estonia powers through with a dislocated shoulder.
node.description: Several days ago he dislocated his right shoulder in training.
node.content: ["There was no stopping the Estonian skater Aleksandr Selevko from competing in the short program today, though he had more than enough reason to pull out of the event. Several days ago he dislocated his right shoulder in training, yet still powered through his jumps. The program was watered down and had mistakes, of course, but he showed up here and that\u2019s what matters. He waved to the crowd with only his good arm."]
